import DocsLayout from "../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Pattern: Family App">
  <h1>Build a Family App with EntDB</h1>
  <p>Complete example: shared family planner where parents are admins, kids are members, everyone sees shared content, and private items stay private.</p>

  <h2>How it maps</h2>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Concept</th><th>EntDB primitive</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Family</td><td>Tenant (type=family, multiple owners)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Parents</td><td>Tenant owners (can manage members)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Kids</td><td>Tenant members</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Shared grocery list</td><td>Node with tenant_visible=true</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Kid's private diary</td><td>Node with tenant_visible=false</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Personal items</td><td>Nodes in personal tenant (separate)</td></tr>
  </table>

  <h2>1. Create the family tenant</h2>
  <pre><code># Parent creates the family tenant
family = await db.create_tenant("smith-family", "Smith Family")
# Parent is automatically the owner

# Add family members
await db.add_tenant_member("smith-family", "user:eve", role="owner")    # other parent
await db.add_tenant_member("smith-family", "user:kid1", role="member")  # child
await db.add_tenant_member("smith-family", "user:kid2", role="member")  # child</code></pre>

  <h2>2. Shared vs private content</h2>
  <pre><code># Shared grocery list — everyone sees it (tenant_visible=true in schema)
plan = db.atomic("smith-family", "user:dave")
plan.create(GroceryList, {"{"}name": "Weekly Shopping"{"}"}, as_="list")
plan.create(GroceryItem, {"{"}name": "Milk", "quantity": 2{"}"}, as_="item")
plan.edge_create(ListHasItem, from_="$list.id", to="$item.id")
await plan.commit()

# Kid's diary — only they can see it (tenant_visible=false in schema)
plan = db.atomic("smith-family", "user:kid1")
plan.create(DiaryEntry, {"{"}body": "Today was a good day"{"}"})
await plan.commit()
# Only kid1 sees this. Parents CANNOT read it (admin != data access).

# Family calendar — visible to all
plan = db.atomic("smith-family", "user:eve")
plan.create(CalendarEvent, {"{"}title": "Family Dinner", "date": "2026-04-15"{"}"})
await plan.commit()
# All family members see this.</code></pre>

  <h2>3. Personal items in personal tenant</h2>
  <pre><code># Dave's work meetings — in his PERSONAL tenant, family can't see
plan = db.atomic("dave", "user:dave")
plan.create(CalendarEvent, {"{"}title": "Board Meeting", "date": "2026-04-14"{"}"})
await plan.commit()

# The app shows Dave two contexts:
# "Home" → smith-family tenant (family stuff)
# "Personal" → dave tenant (work stuff)</code></pre>

  <h2>4. Privacy model</h2>
  <pre><code>Admin (parent) can:
  - Add/remove family members
  - Change roles
  - Manage settings

Admin (parent) CANNOT:
  - Read kid's diary entries
  - Browse all content in the tenant

This is by design. Admin manages the tenant, ACL controls the data.
Same as Google Workspace: admin manages org, can't read emails.</code></pre>

  <h2>5. Schema for family app</h2>
  <pre><code>message GroceryList {"{"}
    option (entdb.node) = {"{"}
        type_id: 1
        tenant_visible: true           // everyone sees
        data_policy: DATA_POLICY_PERSONAL
    {"}"};
    string name = 1 [(entdb.field) = {"{"}required: true, pii_false: true{"}"}];
{"}"}

message DiaryEntry {"{"}
    option (entdb.node) = {"{"}
        type_id: 2
        private: true                  // only owner sees
        data_policy: DATA_POLICY_PERSONAL
    {"}"};
    string body = 1 [(entdb.field) = {"{"}required: true, pii: true{"}"}];
{"}"}

message CalendarEvent {"{"}
    option (entdb.node) = {"{"}
        type_id: 3
        tenant_visible: true
        data_policy: DATA_POLICY_PERSONAL
    {"}"};
    string title = 1 [(entdb.field) = {"{"}required: true, pii_false: true{"}"}];
    string date = 2  [(entdb.field) = {"{"}pii_false: true{"}"}];
{"}"}</code></pre>

  <h2>6. What happens when kid deletes account</h2>
  <pre><code>db.delete_user("user:kid1")
# → kid1's personal tenant: DELETED (all personal data gone)
# → smith-family tenant: kid1's diary entries → DELETED (data_policy=PERSONAL)
# → smith-family tenant: kid1's contributions to grocery lists → ANONYMIZED
# → kid1 removed from tenant_members
# → All automatic. Zero application code.</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
